    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-17T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/764: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-17T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 17—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. My 76, March 12, 11 a.m., and 78, March 13, 6 p.m. Cabinet has not yet
                    adopted Karakhan-Wang agreement. Cabinet intimates in [apparent omission] that
                    the hitch is over Mongolia but political and personal rivalries in the
                    Government probably more potent. From best available Soviet sources it is
                    learned Karakhan has placed time limit on negotiations which is to expire March
                    19th. Koo confirms this confidentially to the extent of saying there was a time
                    limit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
